other_tests.findings: Significant levels of IgG antibody (1120 EIA U; reference range, !12 EIA U) to Bartonella henselae; IgM antibody was negative.

Marked levels of IgG and IgM antibodies to Coxiella burnetii phases I and II (titers of IgG antibody to phases I and II, 1:16,192; titer of IgM antibody to phase I, 1:256; titer of IgM antibody to phase II, 1:16).
Seropositivity to a broad range of pathogens, including R. rickettsii, Ehrlichia chaffeensis, Bartonella quintana, B. henselae, and the agent of human granulocytic ehrlichiosis.
